<subSubSection box="[144,524,202,226]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph blockId="4.[144,524,202,226]" box="[144,524,202,226]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Vernacular names: Piazian, Anjorai</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[144,768,259,411]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[144,292,259,283]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Distribution:</emphasis>
Previously only reported as endemic from S. 
<collectingCountry box="[182,312,291,315]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
in the province Qandahar (
<bibRefCitation author="Wendelbo, P." bookContentInfo="76" editor="Rechinger, K. H." journalOrPublisher="Graz, Austria" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" refId="ref4504" refString="Wendelbo, P. 1971. Alliaceae. In: (Ed.): Rechinger, K. H. Flora Iranica. No. 76. Graz, Austria." title="Alliaceae" type="book" volumeTitle="Flora Iranica" year="1971">Wendelbo, 1971</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Breckle, S. W. &amp; I. C. Hedge &amp; M. D. Rafiqpoor" bookContentInfo="597 pp." box="[212,430,323,347]" journalOrPublisher="Scientia Bonnensis, Germany" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" refId="ref4103" refString="Breckle, S. W., I. C. Hedge and M. D. Rafiqpoor. 2013. Vascular Plants of Afghanistan - an Augmented Checklist. Scientia Bonnensis, Germany. 597 pp." title="Vascular Plants of Afghanistan - an Augmented Checklist" type="book" year="2013">
Breckle 
<emphasis box="[303,358,323,347]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">et al.</emphasis>
, 2013
</bibRefCitation>
). Newly found in 
<collectingCountry box="[624,714,323,347]" name="Pakistan" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
near the village Appozai, Qamardin Karez, Chukhan and Shaghala in the Zhob district.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[144,767,451,507]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[144,243,451,475]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Ecology:</emphasis>
Usually found in sandy to sandy gravel soil in the plains
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[144,768,542,598]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[144,301,543,567]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Ethnobotany:</emphasis>
The whole plant is edible, especially the leaves are collected and eaten as salad.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
